main event: A UFO was reported near Fairfield, Illinois on October 9, 1963.
interesting points: The object was a dark, elongated oval approximately 20-25 feet in length, with internal illumination and no audible sound.
The object hovered at an estimated altitude of 100-200 feet before accelerating rapidly and disappearing.
Photographic evidence was obtained and sent to the USAF for analysis.
A preliminary report described the object as a clay-limestone concretion, which is a common terrestrial object found in the Pennsylvanian strata of Illinois.
Further investigation and analysis of the photographic evidence was required to classify the sighting.
sighted object: a dark, elongated oval object with internal illumination
